  "text": "In what follows we use language models for several purposes. Let p Dir[μ] z (•) denote the Dirichlet-smoothed unigram language model induced from text z, with smoothing parameter μ [CITATION_1] ; unless otherwise stated, μ = 1000 [CITATION_2] . Setting μ = 0 results in a non-smoothed maximum likelihood estimate that is used for (i) the corpus unigram language model, (ii) computing document entropy, and (iii) measuring interdocument similarities and language-model-based documentquery similarity, as described below.",
